 A row is brewing in ANC circles in the Western Cape over the actions of council members in the Kannaland Municipality. ANC councillors now hold the two senior positions but exactly how they got these roles is being questioned by their leaders. Ayesha Ismail reports. Courtesy #DStv403 KANNALAND - A row is brewing in ANC circles in the Western Cape over the actions of council members in the Kannaland Municipality. It appears they, without informing the leadership, ousted mayor Jeffrey Donson and his deputy Werner Meshao of the Independent Civic Organisation of South Africa. WATCH: ANC withdraws from Kannaland coalition Donson is a convicted rapist and Meshoa a fraudster. ANC councillors now hold the two senior positions. WATCH: Kannaland Municipality | Two questionable leaders in office But exactly how they got these roles is being questioned by their leaders. * eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports.